    ('ingles','gramatica',2,'Simple Past',30,'{"questions":[{"type":"choice","prompt":"She _____ TV yesterday.","options":["watch","watchs","watched","watching"],"answer":2,"explanation":"No Simple Past verbos regulares recebem -ED."},{"type":"choice","prompt":"They _____ to the park on Sunday.","options":["walk","walked","walking","walks"],"answer":1,"explanation":"Walk → Walked no Simple Past."},{"type":"choice","prompt":"Qual palavra indica passado?","options":["Tomorrow","Now","Yesterday","Always"],"answer":2,"explanation":"Yesterday = ontem, indica Simple Past."},{"type":"match","prompt":"Conjugue no passado:","pairs":[{"left":"play","right":"played"},{"left":"work","right":"worked"},{"left":"study","right":"studied"},{"left":"stop","right":"stopped"}],"explanation":"Verbos regulares no Simple Past!"},{"type":"choice","prompt":"I _____ English last night. (study)","options":["study","studyed","studied","studying"],"answer":2,"explanation":"study → studied (Y vira IED)."}]}'),

